<p>In my <code>WIX</code> setup (version 3.10) project I rename the MSI using the script below. Then I reference this setup project in my bootstrapper project:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;MsiPackage Id="MyMSI" SourceFile="$(var.Setup.TargetPath)" Vital="yes" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>This results in a compilation error. <code>Light.exe</code> cannot find the output file:</p>  <pre><code>error LGHT0103: The system cannot find the file 'X:\Setup\bin\x64\Release\Setup.msi'. </code></pre>  <p>Here's the script that successfully renames the output MSI before it is compiled:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;!-- Setup.wixproj --&gt; &lt;Target Name="BeforeBuild"&gt;     &lt;GetAssemblyIdentity AssemblyFiles="$(SolutionDir)$(Configuration)\MyApp.exe"&gt;       &lt;Output TaskParameter="Assemblies" ItemName="AssemblyVersion" /&gt;     &lt;/GetAssemblyIdentity&gt;     &lt;CreateProperty Value="$(OutputName).$(Platform).Setup.%(AssemblyVersion.Version)"&gt;       &lt;Output TaskParameter="Value" PropertyName="TargetName" /&gt;     &lt;/CreateProperty&gt;     &lt;CreateProperty Value="$(TargetName)$(TargetExt)"&gt;       &lt;Output TaskParameter="Value" PropertyName="TargetFileName" /&gt;     &lt;/CreateProperty&gt;     &lt;CreateProperty Value="$(TargetDir)$(TargetFileName)"&gt;       &lt;Output TaskParameter="Value" PropertyName="TargetPath" /&gt;     &lt;/CreateProperty&gt;     &lt;PropertyGroup&gt;       &lt;DefineConstants&gt;BuildVersion=%(AssemblyVersion.Version)&lt;/DefineConstants&gt;     &lt;/PropertyGroup&gt;   &lt;/Target&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Compiling under Visual Studio 2013.</p>